pillars of OOPS
abstraction - hide complexity and hide unnecessary details from client(eg- prog lang like c++/java)
encapsulation - bind method and data together like a capsule, data security using access modifiers 
public- can access from anywhere
protected- accessed within the class and by child class
private- only acessed within the class
